<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Certain2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Certain,</orth> adv., certainly, assuredly: <cit><quote>I'll send him c. word of my success,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 1.4.89" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 4, 89</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>'tis c. so,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.181" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 181</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>c., said she, a wise gentleman,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.166" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 166</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his leg is too big for Hector's; more calf, c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.645" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 645</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a man so breathed that c. he would fight,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.645" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 645</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>this beauteous lady Thisby is c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.131" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 131</bibl></cit> (oxytone, and rhyming to <emph>plain</emph>). <cit><quote>Lorenzo, c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 2.6.29" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 6, 29</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>most c. you do usurp yourself,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.199" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 199</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tn 2.3.66" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.362" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 362</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.578" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 578</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 1.59" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.4.130" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 4, 130</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.4.71" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 4, 71</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.189" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 3, 189</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.5.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 5, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.1.123" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 1, 123</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>